<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 04 at 1:42AM EST  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central Floyd,
Gordon and northwestern Bartow Counties through 215 AM EST...
At 141 AM EST, a strong thunderstorm was over Shannon, or 8 miles
northeast of Rome, moving northeast at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Calhoun, Adairsville, Plainville, Shannon, Fairmount, Ranger,
Sonoraville, Pinson, Redbud, Folsom, Audubon, Oakman and
Nickelsville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
